{"serial": "38002", "department_serial": 36, "code": "ER5034", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Photovoltaics Engineering", "ch": "太陽光電工程"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Wu, Jiunn-Chi"], "ch": ["吳俊諆"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 4, "session": ["2", "3", "4"]}, "loc": {"building": "E2", "room": "306"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 25, "department": {"ch": "能源工程研究所碩士班", "en": "MSc in Energy Engineering"}, "system": {"ch": "博士班", "en": "Doctoral Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 0, "selected": 25, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "本課程教學目標在於讓學生認識太陽電池的原理、太陽光電(photovoltaics)系統和太陽光電的應用。這門課在最初幾個章節將著重探討太陽光電過程中最重要的二個部分—作為能源來源的太陽光，以即將光能轉換為電能的太陽電池本身的性質。接下來則會提及太陽電池和模組的製造技術，其後是各類太楊光電系統的介紹，包括太陽能汽車、住宅的獨立型電源供給，以及大規模併網電廠等。", "en": "\"Photovoltaics (PV) are the process of converting sunlight (solar radiation) directly into electricity using solar cells. This course is to provide students with the basic information needed to understand first the resource of solar energy, the principles of PV system operation, to identify appropriate applications and to address simple PV system design.\""}, "outline": {"ch": "這門課是英語授課，授課內容請參考英文說明", "en": "\"This course starts from the resource of solar radiation and basics of solar cell (semi-conductors and p-n junctions, and physics of solar cell, interconnection and PV module fabrication) will be introduced next. The rest of course covers application of PV, including stand-alone PV systems, grid-connected PV systems, PV technology (Si-based, thin-film, and third generation), and PV system economics and ecology. 17 chapters will be covered:\n1. Course introduction\n2. Status & prospects of PV technology\n3. The working principle of a solar cell\n4. Electrodynamic basics\n5. Solar radiation\n6. Basic semiconductor physics\n7. Generation & recombination of electron-hole pairs\n8. Semiconductor junctions\n9. Solar cell parameters & equivalent circuit\n10. Losses and efficiency limits\n12. Crystalline silicon solar cells\n13. Thin-film solar cells\n15. PV modules\n17. Introduction to PV systems\n18. Location issues\n19. Components of PV systems\n20. PV system design\""}, "textbook": {"ch": "\"Smets A., J?ger K., Isabella O., van Swaaij R., Zeman M., Solar Energy: The physics and engineering of photovoltaic conversion, technologies and systems, UIT, 2016.\"", "en": "\"Smets A., J?ger K., Isabella O., van Swaaij R., Zeman M., Solar Energy: The physics and engineering of photovoltaic conversion, technologies and systems, UIT, 2016.\""}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "100", "en": "100"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授", "en": ["Lecture"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "參考英文說明", "en": "\"1. Attendance (10%): Classes are mandatory. All excused leaves require proof.\n2. Homework (50%): Homeworks will be assigned throughout the course, with each corresponding to the content just introduced.\n3. Midterm (20%)\n4. Final exam. (20%)\""}, "officeHour": {"ch": "\"8:00-9:00, 週一至週五\"", "en": "\"8:00-9:00, Monday to Friday\""}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "18", "en": "18"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "domain": {"ch": "熱流與能源科技", "en": "熱流與能源科技"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "專業知識與技能", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習"]}, {"competencies": "實驗規劃與資料分析", "rating": "(0)無", "assesments": ["無"]}, {"competencies": "工程設計與整合", "rating": "(0)無", "assesments": ["無"]}, {"competencies": "合作溝通與管理", "rating": "(0)無", "assesments": ["無"]}, {"competencies": "專業倫理與社會責任", "rating": "(0)無", "assesments": ["無"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "Engineering Knowledge and Problem Analysis", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Test/Exam", "Assignments"]}, {"competencies": "Experiment and Implementation", "rating": "(0)", "assesments": ["No assessment"]}, {"competencies": "Design / Development of Solution and Investigation", "rating": "(0)", "assesments": ["No assessment"]}, {"competencies"